result.execSummary:
The defendant Eduardo L Corral was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Criminal Damage to Property, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Bond to be applied to restitution first.

Pay costs and DNA surcharges each count. If probation is discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil Judgment will be entered against the Defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due. All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. Per Wisconsin Statute, funds from prison accounts may be used for obligations in accordance with prison policy not to exceed 25% of gross.
No contact with victim, except for apology letter.

Maintain absolute sobriety with regards to alcohol and illegal drugs.
  Do not possess or consume alcohol or be on premises where alcohol is served/sold as its primary business except within scope of your employment.
  Must sign release form for all treatment providers.  Sign all releases of information for all doctors and other treatment providers and pharmacy.
Engage and comply in any other counseling including Anger Managment as recommended by the Agent.
Provide DNA sample and pay DNA surcharge on each counts.
Apology letter to be given to Agent first.

timeConds.notes:

60 days to start jail sentence and go today to get start date.
